  "title": "Senior Quantity Surveyor (Consturction)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for taking and analysing measurements, as well as reviewing tender documentation. </li>\n  <li>Implement procurement strategies and review returned tender documents. </li>\n  <li>Reviews cost estimates and cash flow forecasts to communicate updates to relevant stakeholders. </li>\n  <li>Manages the complete post-contract administration processes. </li>\n  <li>Leads project meetings with customers and supports with dispute resolution matters when required. </li>\n  <li>Builds relationships with customers and liaises with contractors, specialists and sub-contractors to help develop resource plans and monitor costs and profitability of construction works to deliver the customers’ and/or project objectives.</li>\n  <li>Analyse Building Information Modelling (BIM) models to validate cost plans.</li>\n  <li>Review documentation to invite tenders from contractors, specialists or sub-contractors on a competitive or negotiated basis.</li>\n  <li>Review valuations and recommendations for interim payments to contractors, specialists and sub-contractors.</li>\n  <li>Review and price assessment of variation cost claims.</li>\n  <li>Review final accounts.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Recognized Degree in Quantity Surveying or Building or equivalent preferable.</li>\n  <li>Possesses knowledge of the industry, construction materials, procurement methods and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Possess strong numeracy, analytical and problem-solving skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
